  "prompt": "Is there such a thing as an agnostic theist?",
  "response": "Yes, there is such a thing as an agnostic theist. An agnostic theist is someone who believes in the existence of a deity or deities but acknowledges that the nature or existence of that deity is ultimately unknown or unknowable. In other words, they hold a belief in God or gods while also maintaining that human knowledge is limited and that certainty about divine matters is not achievable.\n\nThis position combines aspects of theism (belief in God) with agnosticism (the view that certain metaphysical claims, such as the existence of God, are unknown or unknowable). Agnostic theists may feel that while they believe in a higher power or spiritual essence, they are open to the idea that definitive proof or understanding of that being is beyond human grasp.",
